 {"id":"franken_networkx-dm4o","title":"parity: Graph.to_directed() should preserve NetworkX directed edge order","description":"Graph.to_directed() currently materializes directed edges in a different observable order than upstream NetworkX. On undirected insertion sequence a-b, b-c, d-a, FrankenNetworkX yields directed edges [('c','b'), ('a','d'), ('a','b'), ('b','a'), ('d','a'), ('b','c')] while NetworkX yields [('a','b'), ('a','d'), ('b','a'), ('b','c'), ('c','b'), ('d','a')]. Match the upstream directed edge-order contract for Graph.to_directed().","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T08:16:57.149592627Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T08:16:57.149592627Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
